        <briefdescription>
<para>This function sends IPI request to get the PCR value from requested PCR. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>InstancePtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>- Pointer to the client instance </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>PcrMask</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>- Mask that tells which PCR to be read based on the bits set (bit 0 corresponds to PCR 0)and how many PCRs to be read using the number of bits set. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>PcrBufAddr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>- Address of the buffer to store the requested PCR contents </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>PcrBufSize</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>- Buffer size to read the PCR values</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS - If PCR contents are copied</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE - Upon any failure </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
